  <body>
    <segment id="1" parent="12" relname="span">
I believe intuitiveness with regards to HCI can be defined as how 
quickly or how easily one can grasp a particular concept. </segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="8" relname="circumstance">
When it 
comes to an interface being intuitive</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="11" relname="span"> I think that it depends on a 
person experiences, and cultural differences. </segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="10" relname="span">
The more familiar a 
person is with a concept the more intuitive an interface can be. </segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="5" relname="concession">
Companies such as Microsoft ATTEMPT to make their products intuitive,</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="4" relname="span">
but I believe that if someone is unfamiliar with a word processor for 
example, 
Microsoft Word would be a learning experience for them </segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="5" relname="antithesis">
rather than something that is intuitive to them.

</segment>
